    <body>
      <section eId="sec_27_3311">
        <num>27-3311</num>
        <heading>Carpet stewardship advisory board</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_3311__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>one representative of carpet producers;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_3311__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>two representatives of carpet retailers;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_3311__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>one representative of carpet recyclers;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_3311__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>two representatives of carpet collectors;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_3311__subsec_e">
          <num>(e)</num>
          <content>
            <p>one representative of a company that utilizes discarded carpet to\nmanufacture a new product;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_3311__subsec_f">
          <num>(f)</num>
          <content>
            <p>one representative of a carpet installer association;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_3311__subsec_g">
          <num>(g)</num>
          <content>
            <p>one representative from a statewide environmental organization;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_3311__subsec_h">
          <num>(h)</num>
          <content>
            <p>one representative from a statewide waste disposal association;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_3311__subsec_i">
          <num>(i)</num>
          <content>
            <p>one representative from the New York product stewardship council;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_3311__subsec_j">
          <num>(j)</num>
          <content>
            <p>one representative from a consumer organization; and\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_3311__subsec_k">
          <num>(k)</num>
          <content>
            <p>one representative from a statewide recycling organization.\n  3. The members shall be appointed as follows:\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_3311__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>two members to be appointed by the temporary president of the\nsenate;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_3311__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>two members to be appointed by the speaker of the assembly;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_3311__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>one member to be appointed by the minority leader of the senate;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_3311__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>one member to be appointed by the minority leader of the assembly;\nand\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_27_3311__subsec_e">
          <num>(e)</num>
          <content>
            <p>seven members to be appointed by the executive.\n  4. Such appointments shall be made no later than the first day of\nJanuary following the date on which this title takes effect. The members\nshall designate a chair from among the members by majority vote. Board\nmembers shall receive no compensation but shall be entitled to their\nnecessary and actual expenses incurred in the performance of their board\nduties.\n  5. The board shall meet at least biannually by call of the chair.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
